<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Unsandboxed by deliberate design.
         Distribution path is Developer ID + notarized, not Mac App Store.

         Why unsandboxed: the V1 FSKit extension requires a /dev/diskN
         backing device, which the app conjures via hdiutil-attach of
         a sparse image. The DiskArbitration + IOKit user-client paths
         hdiutil walks are blocked from a sandboxed process even with
         temporary-exception entitlements, and fskitd's
         openWithBSDName binds the dev-node open to the caller's
         audit token, so we also can't route hdiutil through a root
         daemon (the dev node is then bound to root's
         diskarbitrationd session and the user's open fails with
         EACCES). Doing hdiutil in-process under the user's uid puts
         disk-image session, dev-node ownership, and mount(8) under
         the same uid.

         Future: bump deployment target to macOS 26 + FSPathURLResource,
         then a sandboxed app could feed the extension directly without
         a backing block device.

         Hardened runtime stays on via build settings; this
         entitlements file deliberately carries no sandbox keys. -->
</dict>
</plist>
